06/05/2011
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Polish Prime Minister Donald Tusk, whose country will take over the rotating EU presidency in July, kicked off a Balkans tour on Thursday (May 5th). 
He started in Podgorica, holding talks with Montenegrin counterpart Igor Luksic. 
Dusk said afterwards that during its EU presidency, one of Poland's priorities will be the acceleration of the Western Balkans' accession. 
On Friday, Tusk will be in Belgrade, and in Zagreb on Saturday. 
(Polish PM website, Vijesti, Blic, Deutsche Welle - 05/05/11)
